name: Adrienne La Faye's Paintings
creator: THQMGTjrvtYww8MvA
description:
Painter, Illustrator and Author    
                                                      
Ninety percent of my creativity is born out of who I am, how I'm not accepted and how the world perceives me. Yet, a small innate portion of my creativity was birthed in innocence, which I instinctively protect from the harshness of our society. 


As a social justice advocate and activist, my paintings often depict the lives of people who have been disenfranchised and marginalized. My work philosophically explores themes of racism, homophobia, and gender bias, all based on my truth. 


Over two decades Adrienne La Faye has been known for her timeless pieces that capture the essence of Black Americana in every stroke. Ranging from every day moments we all experience, the back porch, and the not too familiar crack alleys and the ever changing GREEN landscapes of Seattle, WA.

Intersectionality defines me as an African American, an artist, female, lesbian, and ex-drug addict. 

She embraces her own signature style of bold bright colors and sometimes faceless portraits, she embodies realities that border on true grit and works to uphold the gift that speaks to all types of fans, collectors and art lovers nationally. Her work has been graced the walls of many esteemed collectors throughout the nation. She's won many awards, grants and sits on two artist boards.

To purchase any Adrienne La Faye original piece of art or print click on any order button throughout the Website and soon you too will begin your collection.
